Ryan Yarbrough was activated off the injured list and will start for the Rays tonight in Oakland. Yarbrough has been out since the start of the season due to left groin tightness and made two rehab appearances for Triple-A Durham. To make room on the active roster, right-hander Phoenix Sanders, a USF product, was placed on the 15-day injured list due to lower back spasms. (Injured lists for pitchers switched from 10 to 15 days as of May 2 as part of a series of rules changes that were delayed for the first month of the season.) Yandy Diaz is in the leadoff spot, which manager Kevin Cash said for now will be a more regular assignment. Wander Franco, who was pinch-hit for in the ninth inning Monday for precautionary reasons after missing Sunday’s game with right hamstring tightness, is in the lineup playing shortstop. Here is the Rays lineup: And for the A’s: • • • Sign up for the Rays Report weekly newsletter to get fresh perspectives on the Tampa Bay Rays and the rest of the majors from sports columnist John Romano. Never miss out on the latest with the Bucs, Rays, Lightning, Florida college sports and more. Follow our Tampa Bay Times sports team on Twitter and Facebook.